# 8. アタシ達らしい音楽を

Rin: Whoa! So, they're really gonna sign you to a deal?!
Saki: Yup! We're meeting this weekend to discuss it!
Miku: That's amazing. Your dream of going pro might actually come true.
Len: I mean, their solo show did go pretty well.
Luka: Yes, it did. And it's wonderful to hear such good news.
MEIKO: Thank you for dropping by to tell us this, girls.
Ichika: You shouldn't be thanking us. We really should be the ones thanking you.
KAITO: But it's also nearly the weekend, right?
Saki: Yeah! My heart won't stop pounding! I'm already getting kinda nervous about going over to their office!
Saki: What should we wear? Suits?!
Ichika: I agree that we need to show that we're serious, but suits might be a bit much...
Honami: It may actually have the opposite effect.
Saki: Oh, right... Then, we'll be fine in our regular clothes?
Shiho: Also, Saki, you seem a lot better now...
Saki: Huh?
Shiho: You felt scared about what was gonna happen after we went pro, right?
Shiho: But you don't seem bothered by that at all now.
Saki: Oh...
Saki: Yeah... It did bother me a little until just recently... But I feel all better now.
Saki: I figured out a way to deal with my fears like you said, Shiho!
Honami: Hehe... You already found your answer, Saki?
Saki: I did! I mean, I can't straggle behind while the rest of you keep moving forward!
Saki: So... I'm really excited about us going pro now.
Saki: Because we'll probably get to do lots and lots more stuff like Iori and Saku said!
MEIKO: You seem confident, Saki.
Saki: Huh? Y-You think so?
MEIKO: Yes. The look on your face right now tells me that Leo/need will be able to handle whatever comes its way.
MEIKO: As for your solo show... It was good, and I'm guessing everyone there was moved by your performance.
MEIKO: I think that happened because you were being yourselves.
Saki: Being ourselves...?
Honami: Yes, during the last song in particular, we sort of just let ourselves go while we played it.
Ichika: Yeah. I remember noticing that Saki had switched up her sound.
Ichika: That was when I realized how we didn't have to try so hard to sound good. We could just have fun, and that's what makes our music what it is...
Ichika: Once I knew that, things felt so much simpler, and I just had fun singing and playing my guitar...
Saki: Ichi...
Shiho: ... To be honest, we probably weren't as good technically compared to when we played with anemone, but the crowd was really on our side this time around...
MEIKO: Exactly... Music isn't just about technical mastery.
MEIKO: The emotions I felt during that song... You all looked like you were having so much fun while playing it. Again, it was a very moving performance...
MEIKO: It reminded me just how much I love Leo/need...
MEIKO: So, even after you take this next big step, I hope you girls never forget that feeling.
Saki: MEIKO...
MEIKO: Keep up the good work. We'll always be rooting for you, no matter what.
Saki: ...
Saki: Thank you so much!
Miku: This means more and more people might start listening to your music.
Miku: That's so exciting...
Shiho: Thank you very much for inviting us here today. So, regarding our deal...
Shindo: Haha. There's no need to act so formal. Let's keep things friendly since we're going to be working together from now on.
Ichika: Together...
Shindo: As for the details, we'll be going over each part of your contract one at a time.
Shindo: This is going to feel like a tough slug, so I hope you're all prepared.
Honami: Y-Yes, of course.
Shindo: Then, once we've gone over all that, you'll be given a chance to discuss it amongst yourselves...
Shindo: Also, because you're all minors, you'll need to go home and ask your parents or guardians to review it.
Shindo: They'll be more than welcome to contact me directly if they have any outstanding questions regarding this process.
Honami: Understood...
Shindo: Again, there's quite a lot to go over and it's going to take time to review it all...
Shindo: But once you sign after confirming that everything is in order, you'll officially be signed to our label as artists.
Shindo: So, shall we begin by reviewing the stipulations laid out in this contract?
Shiho: Yes, thank you.
Shindo: First, I'll give each of you a copy of it. Here it is...
Saki: Whoa! This font's tiny! Yeah, it's definitely gonna take a lot of time to go through all this!
Saki: But it's full of really important stuff, right? I'll do my best to read as much as I can!
Ichika: U-Um, Saki...?
Shindo: Haha. Like I said, feel free to relax. It'll make my job easier as well.
Shindo: More to the point, if you do sign this contract, I will...
Shindo: I'll be your main point of contact, so again, let's keep things friendly between us.
Ichika: Thank you very much.
Saki: (Once we sign this contract, we'll officially start working as artists for this label.)
Saki: (We'll have our deal... Our dream... We'll finally be pros!)
Saki: (I get that a lot of things are gonna happen moving forward... Some fun and some not so fun...)
Saki: (But I'm not hesitating anymore. And I don't feel scared now. I'm okay...)
Saki: (Wanting our music to be heard and wanting to keep playing music with them... Both things matter to me... A lot.)
Saki: (I'll be fine as long as I don't forget that.)
Saki: (So, I'm gonna keep trying...)
Saki: (Leo/need's gonna keep trying... To move people's hearts with the music we love!)
